==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Winkle
<hw>Win"kle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>wincle</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Any
periwinkle.</def> <au>Holland.</au> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Any one of various
marine spiral gastropods, esp., in the United States, either of two
species of <gen>Fulgar</gen> (<spn>Fulgar canaliculata</spn>, and
<spn>Fulgar carica</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ These are large mollusks which often destroy large
numbers of oysters by drilling their shells and sucking their
blood.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sting winkle</b></col>, <cd>a European spinose marine
shell (<spn>Murex erinaceus</spn>). See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Murex</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Winkle-hawk</ent>⟦br⟧
